sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant Service as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>4443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC / DB / Memory)
    participant Scheduler as Prometheus Scheduler<br/>(every 5s)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Scraper
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh<br/>Payload Processor
    participant KnativeBroker as Knative Broker
    participant KServe as KServe/ModelMesh<br/>Model Server
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant InitContainer as Init Container<br/>(ose-cli)

    Note over InitContainer,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Init Container Setup
    InitContainer->>K8sAPI: oc apply ConfigMap<br/>model-serving-config<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, TLS<br/>Auth: SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>InitContainer: ConfigMap created
    Note right of InitContainer: Registers TrustyAI as<br/>ModelMesh payload processor

    Note over ModelMesh,Storage: Flow 1: Inference Data Ingestion (REST)
    ModelMesh->>Service: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>No Auth
    Service->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>(CSV to PVC or JDBC to DB)
    Note right of Storage: /inputs/data.csv (PVC)<br/>or MariaDB/MySQL 3306/TCP

    Note over KnativeBroker,Storage: Flow 2: Inference Data Ingestion (Knative)
    KServe->>KnativeBroker: Emit CloudEvent<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.request
    KnativeBroker->>Service: Forward CloudEvent<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Service->>Storage: Store inference data

    Note over Scheduler,Prometheus: Metrics Computation & Scraping
    loop Every 5 seconds
        Scheduler->>Storage: Read stored inference data
        Storage-->>Scheduler: Inference records
        Scheduler->>Scheduler: Compute SPD, DIR,<br/>drift metrics
        Scheduler->>Service: Update /q/metrics values
    end
    Prometheus->>Service: GET /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    Service-->>Prometheus: trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir,<br/>trustyai_* metrics

    Note over Client,KServe: Flow 3: On-Demand Explainability (disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>Route: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    Route->>Service: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP
    Service->>KServe: Inference calls for perturbation<br/>8033/TCP gRPC or 80/TCP HTTP<br/>Plaintext, No Auth
    KServe-->>Service: Prediction results
    Service->>Service: Compute LIME explanation
    Service-->>Route: Explanation response (JSON)
    Route-->>Client: LIME explanation

    Note over Client,Service: On-Demand Fairness/Drift Metrics
    Client->>Route: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    Route->>Service: Forward request
    Service->>Storage: Read inference data
    Storage-->>Service: Filtered records
    Service->>Service: Compute SPD metric
    Service-->>Route: SPD result (JSON)
    Route-->>Client: Fairness metric response
